methods.name: Count by group for a categorical variable
methods.description: Count across groups for a categorical variable, based on subject occurrence
methods.label: Grouped count for categorical variable

codeTemplate.code:
method_id = 'methodidhere'
if(method_id == 'Mth_01') {
in_data = df2_analysisidhere |>
    select(anavarhere, groupvar1here) |>
    unique()
df3_analysisidhere <-
  ard_categorical(
    data = in_data
    bystmthere
  ) |>
filter(stat_name == 'N') |>
 mutate(operationid = 'Mth_01_01_n')
} else {
denom_dataset = df2_denomanaidhere %>%
  select(denom_anagroupvarshere)
in_data = df2_analysisidhere %>% 
    distinct(distinctlisthere) 
dataDriven = isdatadrivenhere
if(dataDriven == TRUE){
df3_analysisidhere <-
  ard_categorical(
    data = in_data
    stratastmthere,
    denominator = denom_dataset
  ) } else {
df3_analysisidhere <-
  ard_categorical(
    data = in_data
    bystmthere,
    denominator = denom_dataset
  ) }
df3_analysisidhere <- df3_analysisidhere|>
filter(stat_name %in% c('n', 'p')) |>
mutate(operationid = case_when(stat_name == 'n' ~ 'Mth_02_01_n',
                               stat_name == 'p' ~ 'Mth_02_02_%'))
}

codeTemplate.code:
df3_analysisidhere <-
  ard_continuous(
    data = df2_analysisidhere,
    by = c(byvarshere),
    variables = anavarhere
  ) |>
mutate(operationid = case_when(stat_name == 'N' ~ 'Mth_03_01_n',
                               stat_name == 'mean' ~ 'Mth_03_02_Mean',
                               stat_name == 'sd' ~ 'Mth_03_03_SD',
                               stat_name == 'median' ~ 'Mth_03_04_Median',
                               stat_name == 'p25' ~ 'Mth_03_05_Q1',
                               stat_name == 'p75' ~ 'Mth_03_06_Q3',
                               stat_name == 'min' ~ 'Mth_03_07_Min',
                               stat_name == 'max' ~ 'Mth_03_08_Max'))

subSection.text: Abbreviations: CI, confidence interval; ITT, intention-to-treat; N, number of subjects in treatment arm; n, number of subjects in specified population or group.
[1] ITT population include all subjects randomized to a treatment arm.
[2] Safety population include all subjects who received at least one dose of the study drug.
[3] Per-protocol population include only those subjects who completed the treatment originally allocated and planned without major protocol violations.
[4] Percentages are based on Safety population.
Abbreviations: N, number of subjects in treatment arm; n, number of subjects with given characteristic; SD, standard deviation

Abbreviations: CI, confidence interval; N, number of subjects in treatment arm; n, number of subjects with given treatment duration; NE, non evaluable; SD, standard deviation; Q1, 1st quartile; Q3, 3rd quartile.
[1] Duration of treatment = Number of days from first dose to last dose of study drug for each subject calculated as (treatment end date - treatment start date) + 1.
